A long weekend boom for Durban tourism, following a difficult year for the hospitality industry. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Durban hotels are experiencing a boom with occupancy already at over 60-percent. More than 42,000 people are expected to descend on the city for the Easter period. READ: High traffic expected over Easter weekend The beachfront is currently experiencing the most traffic. eNCA reporter Mawande Kheswa shares more details in the video above.